INSERT INTO `job_roles` VALUES (1,'Frontend Developer','A front-end developer focuses on crafting the visual and interactive components of websites and web applications. They ensure that users have a seamless experience by building interfaces that are functional, visually appealing, and responsive across various devices and browsers. These developers translate static designs into dynamic and interactive experiences using a combination of programming languages and frameworks, like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, Angular, and Vue.js. They work in close collaboration with designers, back-end developers, and product managers to ensure that every element of the user interface aligns with the project requirements. Beyond aesthetics, front-end developers prioritize optimization, accessibility, and performance, making sure websites load quickly and are inclusive for all audiences. Their role requires constant learning to stay up-to-date with rapidly evolving web technologies and best practices.\n\n Responsibilities:\n- Develop and implement user interfaces using modern front-end technologies, such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.\n- Ensure browser and device compatibility through rigorous testing and debugging processes.\n- Optimize website performance for fast loading times and smooth user interactions.\n- Collaborate with designers to transform UI/UX mockups and wireframes into functional web pages.\n- Incorporate accessibility standards to ensure inclusivity for users with disabilities.\n- Stay informed about emerging trends, tools, and frameworks in front-end development.\n- Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to user interface functionality and responsiveness.\n','https://roadmap.sh/frontend'),(2,'Backend Developer','Back-end developers focus on the server-side of web applications, ensuring that systems operate smoothly behind the scenes. Their work involves building and maintaining the infrastructure that powers front-end interactions, such as databases, server logic, and APIs. By designing efficient, secure, and scalable systems, back-end developers allow applications to handle user requests and store data securely. They often work with programming languages like Python, Ruby, Java, PHP, and Node.js, and manage databases like PostgreSQL, MySQL, or MongoDB. Back-end developers collaborate with front-end developers to integrate the user-facing components with server-side functionality, creating a unified, reliable experience for end-users. They are also tasked with implementing robust security measures to protect sensitive data.\n\n Responsibilities:\n- Design and implement server-side logic and architecture using modern programming languages.\n- Develop APIs to facilitate seamless communication between the front-end and back-end systems.\n- Manage databases by structuring schemas, optimizing queries, and ensuring data integrity.\n- Implement robust security protocols to protect against vulnerabilities.\n- Optimize server-side performance to handle high traffic efficiently.\n- Collaborate with front-end developers and stakeholders to ensure smooth integration.\n- Debug and troubleshoot server-related issues to maintain system functionality.\n','https://roadmap.sh/backend'),(3,'Android Developer',' An Android Developer specializes in building applications for the Android platform, ensuring functionality, performance, and a seamless user experience. They design, develop, and maintain mobile applications compatible with various Android devices and operating system versions. Android Developers focus on optimizing apps for performance, screen responsiveness, and feature accessibility. Using programming languages like Kotlin and Java, along with frameworks like Android SDK and Jetpack, they create applications ranging from entertainment apps to tools for business productivity.\n\n Responsibilities:\n- Design and develop high-quality Android applications using Kotlin or Java.\n- Test and debug apps across different Android versions and devices.\n- Collaborate with designers to implement user-friendly and visually appealing interfaces.\n- Integrate APIs and third-party services into Android applications.\n- Optimize apps for performance, battery consumption, and responsiveness.\n- Ensure compliance with Google Play Store standards and guidelines.\n- Stay informed about Android development tools, trends, and updates.\n','https://roadmap.sh/android');
